@startuml
skinparam sequenceDiagram

participant "WebApp" as WebApp
participant "SWData" as SWData
participant "Manager" as Manager
participant "MessageQueue" as MessageQueue
participant "Worker" as Worker
participant "Memcache" as Memcache

note over Manager, MessageQueue, Worker, Memcache
This is just an example.<br>We could got wi go with Celery, but sometimes it's good to hide the concrete engine behind the abstraction layer.
end note

WebApp->>SWData: fetch new collection
SWData->>Manager: schedule a job
Manager->>MessageQueue: execute a job
Manager->>Worker: update job status
Worker->>Memcache: job result
Manager->>SWData: update job status
SWData->>Manager: job result
Manager->>Memcache: job result
WebApp->>SWData: get job status
SWData->>Manager: get job status
Manager->>Memcache: get job status

@enduml